cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation between ancient and contemporary Chinese. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised algorithm for constructing sentence-aligned ancient-contemporary pairs and applies a sequence to sequence model for automatic transfer. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques for the proposed algorithm and model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is possible as the paper deals with corpus alignment and parallel corpus construction. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is also possible as the paper applies a sequence to sequence model, which is a popular deep learning technique for natural language processing.
